ibes the modern as it was lived and experienced by non-elite groups – tailors, seamstresses, shopkeepers, workers – and suggests that their idea of the modern was nurtured by a changing material world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aCivilization, Modern. 0aConsumption (Economics)zSri Lanka. 0aIndustriesxSocial aspectszSri LankaxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Asia / India & South Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311099823840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238243040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782382430423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782382430/original  a978-3-11-099823-8  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK